        ]
      },
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/9/1/8/1",
      "text": [
        ": سمعت أبا عبدالله عليه السلام يقول: إذا بلغت النفس ههنا – وأشار بيده إلى حلقه – لم يكن للعالم توبة، ثم قرأ: “إنما التوبة على الله للذين يعملون السوء بجهالة”"
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.ammaar-muslim": [
          "1. [1/44] al-Kafi: Ali b. Ibrahim from his father AND Muhammad b. Ismail from al-Fadhl b. Shadhan all together from Ibn Abi Umayr from Jamil b. Darraj who said: I heard Aba Abdillah عليه السلام saying: when the soul will reach here – and he pointed with his hand to his throat – there will be no repentance for the scholar then he recited: “Verily repentance is upon Allāh only for those who work evil in ignorance” <a href=\"/books/quran:4#h17\">[4:17]</a>."
        ]
      }
    },
